# Add Plisio USDT (BSC) Dedicated Deposit Addresses

This plan outlines the steps to give every user a dedicated USDT (BSC) deposit address using Plisio, allowing them to fund their wallet via crypto. The system will automatically detect incoming deposits and credit their wallet balance.

## Open Questions

> [!WARNING]
> **Currency Conversion**
> Plisio operates in USD/Crypto, but your internal wallet balance appears to use Naira (`NGN`). When a user deposits 100 USDT, do you want to credit their wallet in NGN based on a specific exchange rate (e.g., 1 USDT = 1,600 NGN), or are we converting the entire wallet system to USD?

> [!WARNING]
> **Plisio API Features**
> Plisio supports creating "Invoices" (where a user types in an amount and gets an address for a single payment) OR a "White Label Wallet" (which gives a permanent, reusable address). I will implement the permanent, reusable address approach since you specifically requested a "dedicated USDT wallet to fund."

